open-e-joviandss-proxmox-plugin (0.11.6-0) stable; urgency=medium

    * New: Scope-typed locking layer (OpenEJovianDSS/Lock.pm) replacing the
      jdssc-internal REST-level lock — per-VM and per-storage method locks,
      per-jdssc-invocation component locks (jdssc_general / jdssc_info) and a
      reserved multipath class; backed by pmxcfs (cluster) or flock (node)
      with a hold-cap / keep-alive / re-entry registry threaded through $ctx.
      Makes concurrent access to a shared Pool from many nodes and clusters
      safe (builds on cluster_prefix + per-storage target isolation)
    * New: jdssc `pool <pool> targets sessions` subcommand (sessions.py)
      listing a target's active iSCSI sessions — evidence source for the
      session-gated recovery detach
    * New: volume_activate rebuilt as a bounded reactivation cycle with
      three-way error classification, a stale-cookie sweep and a
      session-gated last-resort target detach
    * New: Automatic target_prefix re-homing — activating an idle volume
      whose target does not match the configured prefix detaches and
      republishes it under the new prefix; a volume with live sessions is
      left in place until it is next activated while idle
    * New: Shared-target protection — a storage refuses to attach a volume
      onto, or log out of, an iSCSI target another storage is using, refuses
      to tear down a target that has live connections, and rejects a target
      name owned by a different Pool (JDSSTargetInUseException /
      JDSSTargetPoolConflictException, surfaced as fail-fast operator
      messages)
    * New: NFS storage type now requires user_name and user_password; storage
      add fails immediately if no REST password ends up stored, matching the
      block storage type
    * Change: Lock layer reworked into explicit phases (commission → acquire →
      refresh-bracketed execution → release → decommission); the hold alarm is
      re-armed at every refresh point and derived from the lock registry,
      fixing spurious fatal lock errors when a long activation wait under a
      shared VM lock outlived the cluster filesystem's idle-reclaim window
    * Change: Cluster-lock acquisition polls aggressively in the final minute
      before its deadline (interval halved down to a 0.1 s floor) with
      proportional jitter in every phase; per-VM / per-storage acquire timeouts
      raised to 1200 s and hold timeouts to 1620 s for shared storage
    * Change: Each iSCSI portal login during activation is now bounded
      end-to-end and refreshes the held cluster lock, shrinking the unrefreshed
      window to roughly one login regardless of portal count
    * Change: Cloning now takes only the destination guest's lock — a clone
      never modifies its source, so the previous two-lock ordering scheme
      guarded nothing
    * Change: Allocating a disk with an empty name is treated as a request for
      automatic naming instead of creating an unusable volume named after the
      bare cluster prefix
    * Change: Rename jdssc lock classes jdssc_cluster → jdssc_general,
      jdssc_node → jdssc_info; info-tier acquire timeout raised 10 s → 40 s
    * Change: The force-rollback VM/CT tag is spelled force-rollback, not
      force_rollback (shipped as force_rollback since 0.11.4). Guests still
      tagged force_rollback are treated as untagged: a rollback that the tag
      would have forced now stops with the usual "Rollback blocked" message,
      which names the new spelling. No data is at risk — the failure is to
      block, never to destroy — but re-tag any guest that relies on it:
      qm set <vmid> --tags force-rollback  (pct set for containers)
    * Fix: NFS path() returned no owner or format in list context, so
      Proxmox's ownership check always answered "not owned" — qm destroy,
      unlink and detach silently left files on the share; path() now reports
      vmid and format
    * Fix: _rename_volume could report success without renaming — a probe
      failure fell out of the retry loop as a clean exit and the not-found
      handlers named a subclass that is never raised, so Proxmox wrote configs
      pointing at disks that were never created; the exit contract is now
      pinned by tests
    * Fix: Activating a snapshot of a resized parent failed permanently — the
      staged device was compared against the parent's current size, which a
      frozen snapshot export can never match; activation now only requires a
      non-zero staged capacity (which still catches a broken, non-functional
      export), while the resize path keeps its exact verification
    * Fix: Resize recovery no longer aborts on a transient hiccup of its own
      size check, which could abandon an operation that had already succeeded
    * Fix: vm_tag_force_rollback_is_set no longer answers "absent" on a
      tag-read failure — a false "no tag" silently downgraded a forced rollback
      to a blocked one; it now dies loudly, with a bounded retry for transient
      reads
    * Fix: A clone name collision now removes the intermediate snapshot the
      operation created before reporting the error, instead of stranding it on
      the source volume; real user snapshots are never touched on any failure
      path
    * Fix: LUN placement matches the configured target name literally, so a
      foreign target with a similar name can no longer be mistaken for ours and
      receive a volume
    * Fix: REST layer retries a heavily-loaded appliance's dataless GET (200
      with an empty payload) against the next address, instead of returning it
      broken to the caller or retrying the same host forever
    * Fix: on_add_hook returns undef so the PVE 9.x POST /storage result
      'config' object type check passes (Perl was returning its last evaluated
      expression, failing result verification only after the 8.x → 9.x upgrade)
    * Fix: Targeted rescan skips iSCSI sessions being torn down mid-scan
      instead of warning and escalating to a full-bus scan; a device-rescan
      timeout is treated as one failed rescan and no longer aborts the whole
      activation attempt
    * Fix: Activating a volume whose local record carries no recorded size no
      longer emits an uninitialized-value warning; the unknown size is simply
      refreshed from the array
    * Fix: Routine volume_unpublish is no longer logged at error severity,
      where it drowned real failures for anyone monitoring by severity
    * Fix: list_snapshots guid processing
    * Remove: OpenEJovianDSS/Semaphore.pm and the max_parallel_volume_ops
      property — cross-node concurrency is now bounded by the scope-typed lock
      instead of a host-level semaphore

 -- Andrei Perepiolkin <andrei.perepiolkin@open-e.com>, Claude Code (Anthropic AI)  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0200

