    * New: Four timeout classes with per-operation helper wrappers —
      jd_cmd_read_meta (15 s), jd_cmd_read_list (120 s),
      jd_cmd_idemp (270 s), jd_cmd_nonidemp (540 s) (PL-16)
    * New: Cluster-wide Semaphore.pm controlling max_parallel_volume_ops
      across all cluster nodes (PL-17/18)
    * Fix: _rename_volume timeout raised 40 s → 90 s, retries set to 0
      to avoid duplicate rename on retry (PL-4)
    * Fix: _clone_object pre-checks for and removes conflicting snapshot
      before cloning to prevent orphaned ZFS snapshots (PL-5)
    * Fix: Block device discovery loop extended to 160 iterations (PL-6/12)
    * Fix: volume_unpublish / volume_deactivate timeout raised 40 s → 120 s
      (PL-7)
    * Fix: vmstate guard in _deactivate_volume prevents deactivating
      running-VM volumes (PL-8)
    * Fix: Targeted _rescan_target_hosts() replaces rescan-scsi-bus.sh -a
      for faster, lower-impact rescan (PL-9/14)
    * Fix: multipathd del map issued before and after multipath -f;
      add _multipathd_map_exists helper (PL-11)
    * Fix: eval guard in _free_image ensures ZVOL delete still executes
      after a deactivate failure (PL-13)
    * Fix: Multipath retry budget raised 20 → 60; multipathd del map
      issued every 15 attempts to unblock stuck maps (PL-19)
    * Fix: size==0 detection triggers kernel rescan; REST unpublish +
      republish escalation path added for persistent zero-size devices
      (PL-20/20v2)

